<br>
I was sitting in Dreadlands the other day spamming the zone that i was looking for a group.  3 of my guild members who are not to much higher then me in level were near by in a group also.  I had even asked them to let me know when there was an opening.  well a few minutes passed and i was getting sick of waiting so i went and worked on my tailring skill and came back and gave a couple of the guild members in that group some tailor made quivers because i knew they wanted some.  I was low on mana so i sat there to med a little.  In there little group they had 3 warriors (2 of them guild members at level 45) 2 shamens (1 a 39th level guild member) and a 44 level wizard in their group.  <br>
<br>
one of my fellow guild members then asks me if im busy and i tell them no that im not.  then they ask if i can get a friend of theirs from commons and bring them there cuz he didnt know were that place was.  A red flag went up here.  But not wanting to cause any strife with my hesitation i said sure.  Heck i even like porting people at least then im feeling usefull.<br>
<br>
well i get this person and port them back to the dreadlands and take them all the way back to were my guild mates were  and they thanked me graciously.  soon i saw the other warrior in there group say good buy thanks for the group, and all that, and then left.  The open spot in the group was then filled with the warrior I had gone and gotten from commons.  <br>
<br>
So here i am in DL looking for a group then asked by some guild mates to go and TAXI anouther tank clear from commons to replace their warrior that was leaving.  they then had 3 warriors 2 shamens and a wizard again.<br>
<br>
I can understand there desire to want a BETTER group for getting exp.  But this was a low blow, I had to log after this happened i was so frustrated.<br>
<br>
Now someon tell me wizards are fairly balanced for groups and i'll show you one pissed off wizard.  Heck we're not THAT freindly of a group class, not even my own guild wanted me.  I see my self as a decent wizard i dont complain and i can hold my own with learning to balance mana usage with everyone else so im not holding people back.  But even still i have seen a group i was in do better without me then with me cuz they were able to pull faster, cuz they had a more reliable always there sorse of damage.  were as i am a sorce of damage that is only as good as my mana regen in comparison to how quickly they pull mobs.  when a group likes to pull 3-4 mobs at a time for fast leveing and the tanks are fully decked out to handle the hits with a heal now and then.  We wizards are quickly out classed cuz we cant afford to nuke even once on each mob to HELP or we run out of mana even with clerity.  At least this is what ive seen.  so groups would rather have anouther ALWAYS there sourse of damage like a rouge.<br>
<br>
Ok im done ranting, but man im upset.<br>
<br>
Artillis Windruss<br>
