<BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A> at: 5/30/01 5:29:15 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=artillis>Artillis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/01 11:55:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissed by my own guild...</span><hr size=1> Ok i cant argue with the fact that they had a wizard and probably didnt need anouther, i still think things would have gone well with 2 tanks, 2 shamens, and 2 wizards.  I guess i posted this mostly to RANT.  I had been looking for a group there was a slot opening in there group and they had me go fetch a tank for them from west commons to fill the gap.  I personaly think i could have filled it.  maybee not as well as a tank, but then thats why so many of us rant about our class being unfairly balanced isn't it, we tend to get picked last in many situations cuz other classes just do better as a whole in a group.  not all classes necesarly, but most.  <br>
<br>
I guess one of the main things I was trying to bring out in my frustration is the fact that it can be a pain for us wizards to find groups as many of you already know.  And the last thing i want people to think is I can't play my wizard effectively, far from it.  I gain exp quiet well and solo well and even group well many people have told me this.  But that still dosent change the fact that it's a pain to find groups.  Please don't view me as some player who can't play their class and is complaining about something that is their own fault.  Once again i state that i was merely using the situation to emphasise a point on class balance.  please foucus on whole thread not just the story.<br>
<br>
Artillis Windruss<br>
