 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=artillis>Artillis</A> at: 5/30/01 12:11:24 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorvie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orvie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 2:41:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissed by my own guild...</span><hr size=1> Assuming the group was being controlled by members of your guild...<br>
<br>
If you were not invited to replace a non-guild  member that had left, it's time to move on and find a new guild.<br>
<br>
Either they have issues with you personally, or they simply place the importance of leveling and personal gain above guild loyalty.<br>
<br>
Friendship first, save the selfish minded BS for singleplayer RPGs. I'm not impressed by a level 60 player that screwed over others to achieve level and items.<br>
<br>
