Theorv Orcenfoe<br>
44 wizard<br>
United Norrathian Knights<br>
Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucovenantu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Covenant U</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 5:04:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissed by my own guild...</span><hr size=1> Point well-taken Artillus.  I think the first few answers to your post are so ironic.  You post a common themed story to a rant board to indicate why wizards aren't &quot;balanced&quot; and to share your (warranted) personal frustration.  You are dissed out of a group with your own guild because two wizards are &quot;too much,&quot; yet two shaman and three melee are fine.  Gee, I hear the dull thud of a point landing.  <br>
<br>
The point is simple, if balance wasn't at issue two wizards or two anything wouldn't be a problem, it would just be a different style of play.  Personally, with all the stuns and roots an extra wizard gives I'd say it's a push.  In fact what the melee probably didn't want is ping pong, where the wizzies could drop stuff while the melee cut at the MOB's backs.  In fact given the probablility of adds, including spiders, I'd have taken a second wiz in a second.  Dreadland MOBs hit very hard, and even three melee are gonna get walloped.  My guess is the shaman were pushed anyway with healing.<br>
<br>
Another melee was not necessary at that point, merely a manifestation of the melee-centric bullshit our two senior wizards have clearly bought into. /sigh<br>
<br>
So the follow up in the post is two senior wizards suggesting it's either a personal bias or &quot;wouldn't you want one more melee?&quot;  /boggle<br>
<br>
You TOTALLY missed the guys point and then ratified it.  No wonder we're so dysfunctional as a class.    <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
