 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 5:28:28 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wots-signatures.hypermart.net/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissed by my own guild...</span><hr size=1> Ok, Covenant U, you clearly missed the point.<br>
<br>
I wasn't trying to diss him or whatever you thought, I was trying to comfort him and give him and answer as to why this occured. <br>
<br>
What are we dependant on?  Mana.<br>
What are Warriors dependant on?  HP and their weapons.<br>
<br>
Would you rather sit there, in a group, with no Enchanter or Bard, waiting for 2 Wizards to get their mana back?  Or would you rather have 3 Warriors hacking away at a target distributing the damage taken between the three of them?  Again, when I fought in DL with my Cleric and had a heavy melee group I almost NEVER had to heal because the mobs fell so fast and they distributed the agro between all them.<br>
<br>
The fact is, we're good in groups that can't provide mana regen to us.. but we can't perform to the best of our abilities where as a Melee can.  Verant has to do something to make us more desirable in groups w/o mana regen suppliers.. Harvest helps, just not enough.<br>
<br>
Sorry if you took offense to my post, it wasn't meant to be that way.  I shall retract it just for you, Covenant U. <p><BR>
