<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nizzinsaangreal>Nizzin Saangreal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 5:39:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissed by my own guild...</span><hr size=1> Two wizards in a group in DL should never be OOM...  The mana/damage ratio against the total hp of the mobs at that level is great.  Using the lack of a bard or chanter as justification for this sort of melee-centric thinking is simply rediculous.  Its not hard at ALL to keep oneself in constant Clarity if you really set your mind (hehe) to it.<br>
