<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 8:22:05 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissed by my own guild...</span><hr size=1> Rombus doesn't diss people <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   He was sympathetic as am I, that's hardcore and in my opinion its either time to leave the guild or reassess your play style. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uryzak620.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryzak620</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 9:44:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissed by my own guild...</span><hr size=1> A full group w/ a wizzie or two, should never be oom.  If you are, you are playing the class incorrectly, or there was a train of about 4 mobs on you.  It's just a matter of knowing where to nuke and when.  Honestly, I nuke, at most 2-3 times in any fight, unless we are getting overwhelmed, in which case i dump (no pun intended), and save enough for an evac). A group w/ 2 tanks, 2 shammies, and 2 wizzies, is not the best group for DL, but a fairly efficient one (i have been in worse). <br>
 It truly sounds to me like your guild does not have much faith in you except as a taxi service.  I would definitely find a guild that knows the benefits of the wizard.  That was simply rude on their part, and I would let them know it <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usilvius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 11:01:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissed by my own guild...</span><hr size=1> Hmph, I was in DL the other day and there were 3 wizard LFG (me 48, another 48, and a 46) no one wanted us, so you know what we did? We got togeather, and imported a druid to pull for us. Druid would go get something, and with 1 volly of nukes it would go into run mode for the druid to finnish. This died so fast, and none of us ran low on mana. I personaly never went below 60%. Multi-wizard groups are the most efficient there are simply because we can med back the mana we spend by the time another pull comes back. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucovenantu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Covenant U</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 1:24:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissed by my own guild...</span><hr size=1> First, I never said Rombus &quot;dissed&quot; the poster. So Grim, no need to get your knickers in a twist <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Read above, and you and Rombus will see the only time I used the phrase &quot;diss&quot; was to describe what Artillus' guild did to him.<br>
<br>
Samadhi observed that the first wizard didn't seem to have trouble getting into a group.  Sorry, that just seems to have missed the poster's point and is inadequate to explain his guild's behavior.  They had 3 wars 2 shammies and one wiz.  A war leaves and a spot opens.  They not only chose a war but made their guildie a bitch to go and get him.  So I guess Samadhi's point was that we can get into groups easy, but we just can't be in groups with our own.  But the more shammies and wars the merrier.  Silly me, here I thought we had trouble grouping.   Thanks for clearing that up.  In fact, Samadhi's point was less about explaining why they rejected Artillus than it was meant to be inflammatory, but hey, I've read alot of your posts, Samadhi, the self appointed &quot;anti-ranter.&quot;  Typical fare. <br>
<br>
